title: El Castillo
author: OrangeConcrete
pages:
El Castillo, also known
as the Temple of
Kukulcn, is a
Mesoamerican pyramid
located in the ancient
city of Chichen Itza in
Mexico's Yucatn
Peninsula. It is one of
the most famous and
well-known structures
of the Mayan
civilization, and is
believed to have been
built around the --->

9th or 10th century
CE. The pyramid
stands about 30
meters (98 feet) tall,
and was probably
used for religious
purposes. It is a
popular tourist
attraction, and is
considered one of the
Seven Wonders of the
World.
